Population rates fluctuated in Lavelle during the 1940s as birth and death rates increased and decreased. According to the ''Pottsville Republican'', the annual death rates were: forty-one in 1941, twelve each in 1942 and 1943, six in 1944, ten each in 1945 and 1946, and eight in 1947. Eighteen Additionally:<ref>"[https://www.newspapers.com/image/450353513/?terms=Lavelle&match=1 Year's Deaths Show Increase]." Pottsville, Pennsylvania: ''Pottsville Republican'', January 5, 1948, p. 3 (subscription required).</ref>

<blockquote>"The birth rate during 1943 in the Lavelle area increased with 66 births listed compared to 46 in 1946. There were 34 boys to 32 girls born. One baby died at birth."</blockquote>

As of the [[2010 United States census|2010 census]]<ref>{{cite web |author=U.S. Census Bureau |title=TOTAL POPULATION |website=Decennial Census, DEC Summary File 1, Table P1 |date=2010 |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALSF12010.P1?g=160XX00US4241904 |access-date=November 1, 2024 }}</ref> the population was 742 residents. By the time that the 2020 federal census was taken, the town's population had declined to 708.

